install the helm
1. Add the Prometheus Community Helm Repo
helm repo add prometheus-community https://prometheus-community.github.io/helm-charts
helm repo update

2. Install kube-prometheus-stack

This bundle includes Prometheus, Grafana, Node Exporter, Alertmanager, etc.

helm install prometheus prometheus-community/kube-prometheus-stack \
  --namespace monitoring \
  --create-namespace


This will install everything you need for basic monitoring.

3. Check if everything is running
kubectl get pods -n monitoring


You should see pods like:

prometheus-kube-prometheus-prometheus-*

prometheus-grafana-*

prometheus-kube-state-metrics-*
etc

üîç Access Grafana UI (for dashboards)
4. Port forward Grafana (for local access)
kubectl port-forward -n monitoring svc/prometheus-grafana 3000:80


Then open your browser to:

http://localhost:3000


Default login:

Username: admin

Password: prom-operator

You can get the actual admin password with:

kubectl get secret -n monitoring prometheus-grafana -o jsonpath="{.data.admin-password}" | base64 --decode

üìä Start Monitoring Your Applications

Grafana will already have dashboards for:

Kubernetes Nodes

Pods

Cluster status

etc.

You can also:

Create custom dashboards

Add alerting rules

Scrape custom metrics if your app exposes them at /metrics

Would you like to:

Expose Grafana or Prometheus outside the cluster (e.g. via Ingress)?

Add custom app metrics (e.g., from a Node.js/Go app)?

Add alerts to Slack, email, etc.?

Let me know and I can help with that too.


